The paper deals with designing pricing mechanisms for a new model of valuations, which is a problem in mechanism design and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves analyzing hypergraphs and their properties, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of proportional complementarities and market parameters suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with revenue optimization, which is a topic in economics and electronic commerce (cs.EC).
